    = section "Irregularities in the Past Tense" do
      %p Because the past tense stem is the same as the infinitive stem, the many minor verb classes mentioned earlier in the present/future tense are of almost no concern. Except for verbs whose infinitives end in -сти, -зти, or -йкьи, the past tense can be formed regularly from the infinitive.
